Package com.gemalto.idp.mobile.authentication.mode.biofingerprint

Interface BioFingerprintAuthenticationCallbacks

  • @Deprecated
public interface BioFingerprintAuthenticationCallbacks
    Deprecated.
    This interface gives an application maker the capability of using the following fingerprint authentication process and reports the results to the user.
    Since:
    4.0

    • Method Detail

      • onSuccess

        void onSuccess​(BioFingerprintAuthInput bioFPAuthInput)
        Deprecated.
        This callback function is called if:
        • a user is successfully authenticated using fingerprint
        • and an object that represents a biofingerprint data used for OTP computation is initialized successfully
        The user can now use the authenticated bioFingerprint Authentication Input. For example, OTP computation.
        Parameters:
        bioFPAuthInput - represents the authenticated biofingerprint authentication input object.

      • onStartFPSensor

        void onStartFPSensor()
        Deprecated.
        This callback function is called when the Fingerprint sensor has started listening.

        In this callback, application developer shall instruct the user to authenticate with fingerprint. eg. a DialogFragment with message displayed.

      • onError

        void onError​(IdpException e)
        Deprecated.
        This callback function is called if the fingerprint is not correctly configured or an internal cryptographic error occurs.
        Parameters:
        e - an exception object indicating fingerprint authentication problem. An application behavior can be determined according to an exception type.

      • onAuthenticationError

        void onAuthenticationError​(int errorCode,
                           CharSequence errString)
        Deprecated.
        This callback function is called if the fingerprint authentication fails with an unrecoverable error but the authentication operation has completed. For example, If the user has tried with an invalid fingerprint consecutively. For the list of error codes and descriptions, please see:
        Parameters:
        errorCode - the error code of the failed operation.
        errString - the description of the error.
        See Also:
        Section 'Constants' Please note that once a user has reached the maximum number of failed attempts permitted by the system (for example, 5 failed attempts), the sensor will be locked out for about 30 Seconds depending on the OS version and manufacturer before the next attempt can be performed.

      • onAuthenticationHelp

        void onAuthenticationHelp​(int helpCode,
                          CharSequence helpString)
        Deprecated.
        This callback function is called if a recoverable error occurs during the authentication process. An error can be presented to the user using a dialog fragment. It gives the user a chance of re-authenticating. For example, a finger is removed from a sensor too quickly. For the list of error codes and descriptions, please see:
        Parameters:
        helpCode - code of message
        helpString - help string
        See Also:
        Section 'Constants'

      • onAuthenticationSucceeded

        void onAuthenticationSucceeded()
        Deprecated.
        This callback function is called if the authentication of the fingerprint against the enrolled fingerprints is successful - the fingerprint is recognized.

      • onAuthenticationFailed

        void onAuthenticationFailed()
        Deprecated.
        This callback function is called if the fingerprint is read but is not recognized (for example, a wrong finger is placed on a sensor). In such cases, an error can be presented to a user through dialog fragment.
